<h2>Open Data</h2>
<p>SEPTAlking leverages the data and APIs provided by SEPTA to make
regional rail arrivals and departures available over the phone. There
are lots of great resources available from SEPTA for building apps.</p>
<p><a class="btn" href="http://www3.septa.org/hackathon/">Visit SEPTA
&raquo;</a></p>
</div>
<div class="span5">
<h2>Hackathon Born</h2>
<p>SEPTAlking was built at a transit hackathon held in Philadelphia on
October 8th and 9th. Lots of other great apps were built at this events
as well. If you are a transit rider in Philly, these apps are for you.</p>
<p><a class="btn" href="http://appsforsepta.org/">Apps4SEPTA &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
<div class="span5">
<h2>Tropo Powered</h2>
<p>Because it's powered by Tropo, SEPTAlking also supports both <acronym
	title="Short Message Service, or text messaging">SMS</acronym> and <acronym
	title="Instant Messaging">IM</acronym>, making it easy to find out when
your train is leaving or arriving, using whatever modality you find most
convenient.</p>
<p><a class="btn" href="http://tropo.com">Visit Tropo &raquo;</a></p>
